Maori oven
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the remains of an old Maori oven, or that which resembles such remains, found on the Canterbury Plains
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See: cf. Maori hole
